parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel strip can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to unexpected fuel depletion, engine stalling, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge shows incorrect readings
the fuel gauge malfunctions
the fuel strip fractures
the fuel strip needs to be replaced multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump flange can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel pump area
fuel sprays onto the hot exhaust pipe
fuel leaks continuously
fuel smell is present while riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pressure control module can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The fuel pressure control module fails without warning
leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control unit can cause the loss of anti-lock braking capability, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and a higher risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS system shuts off during riding
resulting in reduced braking capability and rear wheel lock
no brake lights
no speedometer
no odometer
and battery drain.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to ABS Pump/Modulator Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS pump/modulator can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The front brake locks up
making it difficult to move the vehicle
and may require bleeding pressure from the brake line to release.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Outlet Quick Connector Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump outlet quick connector can cause gasoline to leak, creating a fire hazard and potential brake failure.
symptoms: Gasoline leaks from the fuel pump outlet
creating a fire hazard and potentially causing skin rash and other injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive shaft can cause the rear wheel to lock up, leading to a loss of control, and potentially resulting in accidents or crashes.
symptoms: Strong vibration in the rear of the motorcycle
pronounced wobble affecting control
drive train locking up
final drive leaking before failing.
